{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Bug|type2=Fire}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Larvesta}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Bug|prevnum=635|prev=Hydreigon|nextnum=637|next=Volcarona|roundleft=bl|roundright=br}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Larvesta\n|jname=メラルバ\n|jtranslit=Meraruba\n|tmname=Merlarva\n|category=Torch\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Bug\n|type2=Fire\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Flame Body\n|abilityd=Swarm\n|ndex=636\n|udex=142\n|u2dex=171\n|height-ftin=3\'07"\n|height-m=1.1\n|weight-lbs=63.5\n|weight-kg=28.8\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Bug\n|eggcycles=40\n|expyield=72\n|lv100exp=1,250,000\n|gendercode=127\n|color=White\n|evtotal=1\n|evat=1\n|catchrate=45\n|body=14\n|pokefordex=larvesta\n|generation=5\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Larvesta\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'メラルバ\'\'\' \'\'Merlarva\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Bug|Fire}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation V]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] into {{p|Volcarona}} starting at [[level]] 59.\n\n==Biology==\n[[File:Larvesta flying.png|thumb|left|200px|Larvesta "flying" using the fire that spits out from its horns]]\nLarvesta is a fuzzy, moth larva-like Pokémon. It has blue eyes in a shadowed face. Its white mane of fuzz encompasses its head and the upper half of its body, while its lower half is brown. It has three pairs of small black legs. There are five red, slightly whorled horns on the sides of its head, which it can use to spit fire as a defensive tactic to deter predators. It has been seen using fire it spits from these horns to fly. Larvesta\'s flames can reach up to 5,500 degrees Fahrenheit in temperature. It lives at the feet of volcanoes, though it was once believed that Larvesta nested on the sun.\n\n==In the anime==\n===Major appearances===\n[[File:Luke Larvesta.png|220px|thumb|left|Larvesta in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\nLarvesta debuted in \'\'[[BW041|The Club Battle Hearts of Fury: Emolga Versus Sawk!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Luke]]. It battled {{an|Cilan}} and his {{TP|Cilan|Stunfisk}} and won. Luke revealed that Larvesta is in charge of special effects when he is making movies.\n\n===Minor appearances===\n{{-}}\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Unova}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW041|Larvesta|Ash\'s Pokédex|Larvesta, the Torch Pokémon. A Larvesta shoots fire from its five horns to repel its enemies. They live at the base of volcanoes.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Best Wishes\'\'|Unova}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Shadow Triad Larvesta Adventures.png|thumb|140px|Larvesta in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nA member of the [[Shadow Triad]] used a Larvesta to attack [[Lenora]] at [[Nacrene City]]. It was later revealed that Larvesta hatched from an Egg that [[Ryoku]] of the [[Seven Sages]] found in [[Unova Route 4|Route 4]]. It first appeared in \'\'[[PS495|The Battle Within]]\'\'.\n\n[[Benga]]\'s Larvesta appeared in a flashback in [[PS541]].\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Larvesta (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=bug|type2=fire}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=V}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=V|reg1=Unova|num1=142|label1={{gameabbrev5|BW}}:|reg2=Unova|num2=171|label2={{gameabbrev5|B2W2}}:}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Black|t=FFF|entry=This Pokémon was believed to have been born from the sun. When it evolves, its entire body is engulfed in flames.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=White|entry=The base of volcanoes is where they make their homes. They shoot fire from their five horns to repel attacking enemies.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Black 2|v2=White 2|t=FFF|entry=Said to have been born from the sun, it spews fire from its horns and encases itself in a cocoon of fire when it evolves.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=Said to have been born from the sun, it spews fire from its horns and encases itself in a cocoon of fire when it evolves.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Y|entry=The base of volcanoes is where they make their homes.