tion]] as Larvesta and its {{p|Volcarona|evolution}}.\n* Larvesta and its evolution are the only Pokémon that are neither {{pkmn2|Legendary}} nor {{pkmn2|Mythical}} that learn a move upon reaching level 100.\n\n===Origin===\nLarvesta may be based on a {{wp|moth}} — likely an {{wp|Attacus atlas|Atlas moth}} larva or a {{wp|Halysidota harrisii|Sycamore Tussock moth}} larva — and the {{wp|Tower of the Sun}}, a famed Japanese monument. The way its red growths are shaped and positioned on its circular body may be a reference to the sun or to the \'\'{{wp|Gozan no Okuribi|Daimonji}}\'\'. It may also be based on a {{wp|torch}} or cigarette.\n\n====Name origin====\nLarvesta may be a combination of \'\'{{wp|larva}}\'\' and \'\'{{wp|Vesta (mythology)|Vesta}}\'\' (Roman goddess of the hearth and home, symbolised and represented by an eternally-burning fire located in her {{wp|Temple of Vesta|temple}}). It may also involve \'\'{{wp|lava}}\'\'.\n\nMerlarva may be a combination of めらめら \'\'meramera\'\' (onomatopoeia for flaring) and \'\'larva\'\'.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=bug|type2=fire\n|ja=メラルバ \'\'Merlarva\'\'|jameaning=From {{tt|めらめら \'\'meramera\'\'|onomatopoeia for flaring}}, and \'\'larva\'\'\n|fr=Pyronille|frmeaning=From the prefix \'\'pyro\'\' and \'\'{{tt|chenille|caterpillar}}\'\'\n|es=Larvesta|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Ignivor|demeaning=From \'\'{{tt|ignis|Latin for \'fire\'}}\'\' and \'\'{{tt|vor|before, pre-}}\'\'\n|it=Larvesta|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=활화르바 \'\'Hwalhwaruba\'\'|komeaning=From {{tt|활활 \'\'hwalhwal\'\'|blazing}} and \'\'larva\'\'\n|zh_cmn=燃燒蟲 / 燃烧虫 \'\'Rán\u200bshāo\u200bchóng\u200b\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=From {{tt|燃燒 \'\'rán\u200bshāo\'\'|to burn, combustion, or flaming}} and {{tt|蟲 \'\'\u200bchóng\u200b\'\'|insect, worm}}\n|ru=Ларвеста \'\'Larvesta\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n<br clear="left">\n\n==Notes==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Bug|type2=Fire}}\